body:
@klsince thanks for connecting the dots. I see that the feature can be useful. Mayank has proposed two approaches to do this. A third (less disruptive code-wise) one is to have minions cleanup the segments via a background task.

Let us discuss a bit on these before you start with the PRs.

Which approach are you choosing and why?

@mcvsubbu We want to support all 3 approaches, and each of them has their own pros/cons

- Force download: Big hammer solution, can be used to fix corrupted segment on server, but costly
- Local cleanup: Cheap, align with the current way of adding/removing indexes on-the-fly when server loads the segment. We don't remove the index right now only because V3 format does not support it. This issue ticket is trying to resolve that.
- Minion cleanup: Powerful, can perform operations that cannot be done locally, e.g. dictionary encoded to raw index conversion, but costly, and requires setting up minion instances

@siddharthteotia and I have been discussing the V3 removal several times, but haven't got a chance to work on it
